reviews_data.review_text: Great place for meeting friends for coffee or lunch. Also perfect for enjoying alone.

8/25
We just returned for another visit!!!  OMG all the pastries looked delish.  We ordered a few pastries and 2 coffees and we were excited to try everything!!!  Everything was delish!  The pastries were so fresh and you can definately share a few things, so you can taste a few desserts.  We cannot wait to come here again.

2024

It has been years since we have been here.  We stopped in today for a coffee and a yummy pastry.  Everything looked so delicious that it was hard to pick just one.  3 coffee’s and 3 treats cost $40, so a little pricey but worth the visit.
Adorable atmosphere and delicious pastries

**Very disappointing experience with hygiene**

I visited Amélie’s French Bakery today and was quite disappointed to see flies on the desserts displayed on the counter. I politely asked the cashier why they weren’t covered, or why they didn’t do something to prevent flies from landing on them—especially since the dessert they’re currently promoting had a fly sitting right on top of it the entire time I stood there waiting to pay (over a minute), and no one did anything about it.

The cashier’s response was that it’s the manager’s decision — they want to promote their new dessert by displaying it uncovered on the counter, and there's nothing they can do about it. She did say she would let them know, but it seems like nothing has been done to address the issue.

It’s really unpleasant to see that in a place where people go to enjoy a treat. I’m concerned about the lack of attention to hygiene and I truly hope they take steps to fix this. It’s unacceptable for food to be exposed like that.

been here 10ish times over the year, vast and best variety, intriguing decor, very loud for studying (bc busy, understandably), macarons w/ flavorful fruit puree, and the kale cranberry salad was one of the best things i've ever had.

The pastries and coffee are great. Lunch is seriously lacking. Some of us had the soup. Very bland and watery. Sandwiches were so so. Nothing to write home about. The biggest problem were the kids meals. Most kids do not like any bread but white bread. Amelies makes a kids PB&J with sourdough. Both kids commented about the bread. They said the sandwich was yucky. The adults tasted it and agreed. From now on, this place will only be for desserts and coffee. Also, many people drink water. Why is there a quart size pitcher to pour from? This looks really time consuming for the servers to keep filling this. Buy a dispenser or bigger container.
My favorite place to get work done.  Staff are always sweethearts.  Caramel brownie is the best!
Great food and great staff! I loved it—they served excellent coffee and delicious French pastries.
Cute place with a beautiful bakery selection. However, it took 20 min to get a small iced latte on a Thursday afternoon.

Overpriced overrated has-been of a bakery. "French" is pushing it a bit, as besides croissants,macarons and a few tarts it seems very Americanized. People who have lived in Charlotte a long time have told me Amelie's used to be good. I went to the other location 3 years ago when I moved here and it had significantly better offerings, though I still was not overwhelmed. I don't appreciate paying almost $5 for a very stale bland almond croissant, though my 4 year old did happily  stuff a macaron in his face, but he likes anything sweet and isn't much of a food critic.
rude staff. completely ignored me while i was waiting for my drink but asked others if they had a drink.

I have been to Amelie's a number of times.  They have good pastries and sandwiches, and a really delicious chicken pot pie soup.  I've gotten things to go, as well as stayed and eaten there. The prices are high, especially since many of the pastries are small. The salted caramel brownie is a popular choice.
My issue isn't with the food, my issue is with the rude staff that I have encounter on my visits there. Upon checking out, you are prompted to tip 20% ++ for extremely minimal service. I bought six items the other day. The worker put them in a box. Why am I being ask to tip so much for simply putting items in a box? She was curt and rude when I pressed 'no tip'.  Putting items in a box is doing the bare minimum and should not accrue a service charge. If you do stay and sit, a server will drop off your food, but no one comes back to check on you. Be aware of that when checking out. This is not a full-service restaurant. There are no refills and you clear your own dishes and put them in a bin. If workers are unhappy with how they're being compensated, then they need to speak to management. Restaurants and cafes do have the ability to turn off this tip feature and the screen, however they choose not to.

First time here, everything looked amazing. I ordered a blueberry muffin, an almond croissant, a sour cream lemon blueberry cake, a cinnamon roll and a peach croissant. Peach where was it? Bland. Cinnamon roll dry and tasteless. Almond croissant very overdone and dry. Blueberry muffin, dry and overcooked. One bite and in the garage they went. Sour cream lemon blueberry cake is the only reason I gave it a star. I really had high hopes
Pastrys were good but the drinks were really really bad

The bakery side the house is great. The food however is not so good, bacon is burnt on both orders, snap and crumble. Coffee is good however didn't come the way I asked, double caramel with no Carmel. Expects 18% tip glad and you have to get your own stuff, they will bring food to table. The workers are pleasant.

OMG stands for Outrageously Magnificent Goodies!  This location has a quaint decor with no two chandeliers being the same and mismatched chairs at the dining tables.  The pastries and lunch sandwiches are always top tier.  Bon Appetit!

Also, if you are eligible, don't forget to ask for your military discount!

reviews_data.review_text: The macarons are fantastic. Lots of great flavors. Great location. Lots of good seating options.
I miss when they were open all night long and I could come eat after working 3rd shift 😋

I really enjoyed my visit to this Amélie's Café--it's much more spacious than other locations I've been to, which made it feel airy and inviting. The space stays true to their French eclectic aesthetic, filled with whimsical, vintage-inspired artwork that adds a quirky charm.

The staff at the pastry counter were friendly and helpful, which made browsing their baked goods a treat. Unfortunately, the experience at the coffee station was less warm--the woman working there wasn't as welcoming, which was a slight disappointment.

We ordered a tiramisu latte, which was just okay--not bad, but not especially memorable. We also tried a half-dozen macarons, and those were hit or miss depending on the flavor. Favorites were the raspberry, café au lait, and birthday cake, while the lavender lemon, blueberry cheesecake, and lemon tasted a bit too artificial and overly sweet.

One thing I did notice was that the tables weren't wiped down well, it was still kind of sticky, even though the café wasn't busy at the time. That said, the overall vibe was cozy and relaxed--a lovely place to enjoy a drink and pastries while catching up with friends.
Once again, the pastries did not disappoint. The salted caramel brownie was delicious, as always.
Love Amelie’s! Great food and pastries; great drinks; great atmosphere; friendly and attentive staff!

Ordered a naked cake a week ago for July 4th after confirming details by phone. My wife and I just went to pick up the cake and received a fully iced cake instead. When we complained, the pastry chef explained he had to ice it because the layers were falling apart but offered no apology or solution.
The final product looked nothing like what we ordered or the picture shown to us. Very disappointing service and no attempt to make it right. Very poorly made cake and service. Even the presentation is poor; we asked for the berries to be in the center.

No one seemed to care at all.
Charming and stylish French bakery with delicious pastries

Atmosphere was fun and warm. Ordered the yogurt with granola and berries with raspberry ice tea. I enjoyed both! The granola was soft it a hint of cinnamon. I like my tea not too sweet and this one was just right. Pricing was not outrageous for portions or quality. Would recommend!

I got a notification that my order was ready… So, I went inside and I could see them put it behind the counter. I was literally 10 feet away from it but could not get to it. The staff did not engage at all. A staff-member asked if everyone was waiting on online or to-go orders. One lady got her attention… but after that, they disengaged. The 10-foot rule is apparently not a thing here. Several staff members passed by with zero acknowledgment of my existence. Again, my order was ready… I was almost to the point of going behind the counter and grabbing it myself! Someone finally asked my name but then disappeared into the kitchen with a dine-in order for someone else. Then, they grabbed another dish for someone else before finally handing me my food. Literally, It would have taken 2 seconds to just hand me my bag! This is not the first time this, or a similar instance, has happened before. I got the notification at 11:23 that my order was ready and it was not placed in my hand until 11:45. All the while, it was sitting on the back counter! The food was excellent! It always is. The kitchen staff is amazing! However… unless I am a dine-in customer… no one seems interested in being helpful. I just don’t think I am going to come back for a while again. I stopped coming after a similar instance happened a while back… only that time they said they put my food on the to-go rack but did not. I was there waiting. Then, they tried arguing with me before I gave up and just left without my food. So, I tried to give a little grace. I really do like the food… it’s just not worth the frustration when I can just go to Chicken Salad Chick and grab my food from the pickup station.
Quiet French bakery.  Very good pastries! Friendly staff

reviews_data.review_text:
Ordered pesto chicken sandwich. Chicken is hard and not cooked properly, I could see pinkish color on the chicken which clearly indicates the chicken is not cooked. Nothing special in the sandwich just sauce, spinach and uncooked chicken breast. Coffee was not that great either. The only good thing is patio seating.
Restrooms are dirty as hell, felt very uncomfortable to use them.
Lovely bakery with yummy treats, sandwiches and decor is pretty too. Customer service was amazing as well!!!

Went there today and the young Asian boy help getting out order together, when checking out at the register before we could type our name for the points he cleared it out turned and walked away very fast. Never had custom service like this before.
Espresso is on point, breakfast sandwiches are a family favorite!

This is the better Amelie’s location for sure. It’s big, packed with people, and the look is nice. I love the tile tables and it’s a good place to sit and work. As for their pastries, it really is a hit or miss whether or not it’s fresh or old. I liked the Petit Gateau last time I got it, it was soft and chocolatey, but this time it was clearly old. The cafe au lait was also just okay. Creme Brûlée is good, it tastes right, and the eclairs are a bit…wet? Maybe that’s how eclairs are supposed to taste, I’m not sure. Again I love the vibe here, and I have never ordered from the menu but I heard the chicken sandwich is amazing, I had a friend who said he comes here once a week to eat just that.
Plenty of space to find a spot to work. Sandwiches and coffee are just ok. Barista was rude

I don’t know how a French bakery screws up a baguette, but this is an extremely bad loaf of sandwich bread in the vague shape of a baguette. No chew, awful crust, just bad.

Desserts look good, but don’t bother with a baguette.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're very sorry to hear that you didn't enjoy the baguette.  We always aim to provide fresh, high quality baked goods, and it's disappointing to learn we missed the mark for you.  Your feedback is important to us, and we'll be sure to share it with our team as well as our bread factory as we work to improve.  If you're open to it, we'd love the chance to make it right-please feel free to reach out to us directly.

reviews_data.review_text: Beautiful decor and WONDERFUL friendly staff.. I spent just under $40.. all of the desserts are gross! Like EVERY single one.. I got a pistachio petit for, took one bit and spit it out.. same with the lemon bar.. strawberry cream cheese danish is ok, probably would be better fresh.. the macarons don’t have a flavor.. I got 4 flavors, strawberry cheesecake, pistachio, birthday cake, can’t remember the last.. but they ALLL just taste like vanilla lol and the crème in the middle leaves a waxy feeling in your mouth.. The crème Brulé was ok at best.. not terrible, but I wouldn’t go out my way to get it again..this is my second time trying them because I like the other locations but I can’t say I’ll be back..
Pastries were really good! Real French decoration and cuisine! HIGHLY RECOMMEND!!!

reviews_data.review_text: Great selection of delicious baked goods, friendly service, lively atmosphere, and quality coffee. However, the bathroom didn’t reflect the overall standard of the café—it felt rundown and had an unpleasant odor."
I had Amelie's cater a corporate event and every detail was perfect.

The food at this establishment is average at best, the eggs are unseasoned, the bacon they use is microwaveable, and the busicut lacks the taste of salt.  The croque monsuier was no longer hot by the time I received it and was not as good as Hot Ham and Cheese from Hardy's. I also tried several pastries. The croissant cookie was excellent, the cinnamon roll was decent after having to heat it up at home. The brownie pastry and lemon raspberry pastry i think you should pass on. It seems the desserts are hit or miss, but  coffee seems to be the best thing here.

A friend recommended Amélie’s French Bakery to us, and we were completely mind-blown! From the cozy and charming ambiance to the delicious food and quick service, everything was absolutely epic.

We couldn’t leave without grabbing a few pastry tarts as a thank-you for our friend who introduced us to this amazing spot. Highly recommend the pecan tart, the potato wrap (because let’s be real—potato lover for life!), the freshly baked croissants, and the perfectly crisp baguette. But the real star? The dark chocolate mocha coffee—hands down the best we’ve ever had!

If you’re looking for a bakery that delivers on both taste and experience, this is the place to be! Can’t wait to come back.

PS got pictures added to apple maps 😉

reviews_data.review_text: The spinach quiche is the best! You can’t go wrong with any items though
This place is wonderful. Great food, service, and ambiance. My favorite cafe in CLT!

The atmosphere is a site to see! Each set of table and chairs are unique. There's a nice collection of needlepoint on the wall for all the craft enthusiasts. I only had coffee and bread from the bakery. I'm looking forward to trying breakfast the next time I'm in the area. Highly recommended!

Always a delightful seasonal assortment of cabinet treats and drink menu, beyond their staple menu. Staff attentive and thoughtful with suggestions, complimenting the thoughtful full use of the floor space in this rather large venue. Only suggestion is for an enclosed seasonal patio to be implemented, as there is plenty of driveway/verge space to push the sidewalk out to to increase capacity during frequent busy periods.

reviews_data.review_text: Adorable French café with some of the best food and pastries I've ever had. This place is a must-try.
Comfortable atmosphere and great layout. And the peppermint mocha latte was the best!

Got several bakery items and two sandwiches (make- your- own bacon egg and cheese on croissant and a ham on sourdough with fig compote and goat cheese and greens). All of our food was delicious and sandwiches prepared promptly.  Lovely atmosphere with whimsical chandeliers, Renaissance art, and quaint music.
Coffee was great. Pastries not so good.
Broccoli cheddar soup and fresh berry salad
Delicious pastries and coffee, as well as an inviting atmosphere.
Soooo amazing 🥰
I got their chicken salad tonight, absolutely no flavor, the very blandness thing I have ate in a long time. I was really looking forward to enjoying it,OMG I need to make a sandwich now.
Frozen half filled macarons were a disaster never again. This location has seen better days.

Asked for a key lime  tart which is my favorite there and it was horrible,  did not have key lime and it was not creamy as it was supposed to be, but sticky.
I asked for a glass of water and glass was nasty, asked for a clean one and got another one worst than first.
Got a lavender latte but it had no flavor. I'm not sure they even put flavor. Waste of money.

Good grwnch bakery and cafe .
Loved ther german chocolate 🎂
Always come here when we come to Charlotte it’s our favorite place in Charlotte (RIP Carmel tort) so good

Amélie's is more than a coffee shop. They have tons of homemade pastries from croissants, pies, tarts, donuts, eclairs, scones, macaroons, and many more to choose from with a cup of coffee or tea. I tried the breakfast wrap that came with eggs, cheese, potatoes, sausage, or bacon served in a sundried tomato wrap. It was steaming hot and delicious 😋! Everything was prepared fresh to order. For an eclectic lunch or breakfast, meet some friends at Amélie's to enjoy coffee and pastries.
Such a pleasant café.  Yummy food & lovely atmosphere.  The staff is very friendly.  Highly recommend.
The place is sooo cute! And I tried my first creme brulee here....it was so good!! I love the creme brulee, and I love the sundried tomato turkey wrap!
Zach was one of the best workers I’ve ever seen. Great service.
We had a great visit yesterday morning at Amelie’s.  My daughter and I enjoyed are food  especially our treats.
Hard to beat Amelie’s for breakfast - great coffee, tasty pastries, and we love the atmosphere!

Absolutely loved the place. We had tiramisu latte and chocolate croissant. It was really good. The interiors were decorated. The rest of the items like pastries and macrons were tempting though we did not eat them.

We were so lucky to have Amelie's be a last minute dessert caterer for us when we had to replan our wedding due to hurricane Helene. The team was incredible in regards to ensuring we had what we needed and providing prompt communication. The desserts were delicious and we received many compliments from our guests.

The macarons are light and flavorful. We got the pumpkin, raspberry, and chocolate ganache. They were a good size!!

Overall recommend checking Amelie's out for your dessert catering needs as well as popping in for a treat
Awesome
Just went in on Wednesday and have to give a shoutout to Emre! Huge help with my friend’s nut allergy and a very kind kid overall. Will definitely be coming back!
The tiramisu filling was more like a jelly than a creamy texture, which was disappointing. The brownie and pecan dessert was overly sweet, far from the balanced flavors typical of French taste.
Quaint and cute French bakery and coffeeshop! We had the lemon berry tart and twice baked almond croissant, with coffee and lavender tea! Spectacular!
Patty is always extremely helpful and very pleasant.  She provides a great customer experience.😊
Food not what it used to be. Soup overcooked and too many onions. Salted Carmel brownie very dry.
wow when i tell you willow is probably one of the kindest people i have ever talked to

Employee was not familiar with pastries. She also didn’t bother on asking for assistance when I had asked about an allergy item. It was not busy at that time roughly around 7:30p. She was not polite, nor welcoming. I’d rather take the ride 30 minutes with traffic than coming to this location, AGAIN!
Such a cute place! Truly a gem of coffee and dessert varieties.  Hours are amazing!  Sandwiches and soups! Would definitely recommend!!
The atmosphere is amazing and fun. The food and coffee were delightful!
I LOVE the vibe of Amelie's, all the amazing pastries, and the chicken salad over the side kale is delicious! Oh! And great tea and coffee. And gorgeous tasty macarons!

This place is so cute and the people working there are very nice, so I hate to give a bad review. I got the french toast and it was the most dry and tasteless French toast I have ever had. The syrup also tasted like cheap off brand syrup from the grocery store. The eggs were also over cooked but I ate it because I wasn’t going to eat the french toast and I was hungry. My husband got the croissant and said it was just alright, but not great. I didn’t try the pastries or coffee, but they all looked delicious.

Patty was amazing, helpful and sweet as soon as we walked up to the counter. The food showed through, we had the quiche Lorraine and fig/bacon/brie tartine. My mouth is watering again thinking about it. Sooo good. Pastries were top notch!

I enjoy this location a lot! It's very spacious on the inside, and they have beautiful pastries. I recommend the raspberry lemon tart as it is very refreshing and light. It's a little expensive (as a college student), but I enjoy coming here. The workers are nice and intentional about service, and it's always clean on the inside.

Update on 9/28/24 went to Amelie's on Pineville Matthew Rd and ordered a "make to order sandwich with turkey, Swiss cheese, Dijon mustard, and spinach to go. However , when we opened the sandwich at home it was missing the spinach, and Dijon mustard. Disappointing service today!

Updated (5/10/24) to old review. I ordered one of my favorite desserts "Fresh Fruits Tart". I have had this tart many times, but today it was gravely different "water down, lighter color, and nasty taste." What happened to my favorite desserts!   See picture -- changes to a perfect dessert is never good!

Lower rating required for messing up my dessert.
Nice cozy cafe with pretty big menu. Not only pastries but also some salads and real food.
Overrated. Nothing special. Foods not great and the place is just uninspired.

Love this place. The twice baked croissant is so delish. And the quiche is so yummy.  😋 this place is definitely a must go to and try. Great friendly staff. Nice and clean and brightly lit. Weather permitting, you can sit outside as well.

It’s a cozy place to hang out and grab a cup of coffee. The Oreo Cream Cheese and Pecan Croissant are my favorites, although I usually get my desserts to take away but this place is nice to stay and chat.

I clearly asked for a CHOCOLATE mousse, not a vanilla one. (I came 7/25/24 at 9:15am, if you want to tell the young guy with dark hair that took my order to get his ears checked). I absolutely hate vanilla. I tried it, and it tasted very fake, barely masking the hydrogenated soy bean oil in it. I tried a bit on the top, and it was so gross that I just threw it away. We ordered in, and my drink came in a to go cup, and my friend's came in an actual glass. There goes getting any actual cute photos. Make up your mind. My friend ordered a hot chocolate, which wasn't bad, albeit plain all things considered. My chai latte was gross. It had almost no spices in it, which is why I suspect they put a ton of cinnamon on top, to try and mask this. It basically just tasted of steamed milk, which is freaking gross. I live in a pretty small city, and there is WAY better chai lattes there than this place. Waste of money.

Also, do something about the ants on your patio that are eating your customers when they sit outside.
I tried the Napoleon cake, it was not bad. Definitely one time try

Always have a lovely experience at this shop. Super friendly and nice staff and always clean. Well decorated and light up for just a perfect start to your morning eating a macaroon while sipping on coffee. Enjoy and cheers!!
Greedy, avaricious owners charging $0.50 cents for tap water.

Why did your Cafe begin to charge for water? I am not going to pay extra for a 12 Oz cup of water especially as they used to have it available for free. Seems like they may have some management/financial issue behind the scenes…Sad that a respected restaurant would do this.
More expensive on their desserts than I usually pay....very good though
Pastries are so delicious
Amelie's is my favorite coffee shop and bakery in the area. Their espresso is really good. The macaroons are 🔥. Don't sleep on the salted caramel brownies either.

The cappuccino and pastries were good.  However, there was a swarm of flies inside the glass where the sweets were located.  This was pointed out to an employee who responded “I know”.   We also noted the crescent rolls that were sitting out were combined with the fresh.  Seeing this was quite disappointing.

This is a nice little place around Pineville. If you are looking for coffee date or just wanted to try some good coffee and other French treats then this is the place for you. Baked Almond croissant was so good, you should not miss that. Macaroons
were also delicious. This place has really nice inside and outside seating with good Atmosphere. Need to go back and try some more items. Overall 4.25/5 ⭐️

20240528: Amelie's has wonderful pastries, coffee, and French bistro food. I like the macarons and coisants with cafe au lait.

For my birthday, Amelie's sent me a $5 birthday coupon, which covered most of the cost of this wonderful macaron and decaf coffee.
Horrible place the employees flirt with customers and sleep with married men Christopher is disgusting at this location don’t take your men there
The food and sweets are great! Went there on a rainy day and the concrete floor was a bit slippery from the water. You order at the counter and they bring the food to your table.
Very nice people, great food, reasonable prices! Loved it
Good coffee and  dessert.Too often there is a broken coffee machine and therefore no coffee .
The atmosphere takes you to a quaint little corner of France. The pastries are delightful and delicious.
Love the pastry here even though it is a bit pricey.  Wish there was one nearer to me.

The kid who delivered our food, his name is Joey. He was so pleasant & asked us what else we needed.
In this day where service sucks everywhere it was was awesome to have a smiling face like Joey’s
Great quality foods ,fresh,friendly staff. Atmosphere 100 %
There were multiple gnats in the display case and something fuzzy stuck to my eclair. I usually have no complaints with Amelie's but I'm a bit put off after today. Always a great atmosphere, though

One slice of roast beef and one be slice of cheese cold for $12, tomato soup has the worst taste, broccoli soup is all water, coffee tasted so old and just gross.  $30 for total garbage.  Service was delightful which was lovely.
The best service aver. The food is amazing I had Zahra took my order she is so professional and very knowledgeable and helpful.

The coffee was horrible. The person who makes it needs to know that it can’t be so strong that we can’t drink without diluting it with water. Unfortunately they didn’t keep hot water but it was cold and we ended up with cold coffee.
Wonderful pastries and coffees! Great selection of other drinks, teas and food.
First time coming on a late evening and the hot chocolate and pastries were delicious! It wasn’t too busy. Nicely decorated too.

My experience:

Ambience is pretty nice, service is great.

Food and drinks - not great.

1. I ordered light roast coffee - it's bitter than the dark roast.

2. Brownie tart(?) Is hard, I expected a brownie to be soft, but it was hard - but the representative helped me reace with the espresso one. It's tasty.

Eclair is nice.
Everything here is delicious 🤤 I’ve never ordered anything I didn’t enjoy!

reviews_data.review_text: Not sure why this amelies location is charging $5 for lettuce, tomato and basic toppings that come on a sandwich, but these items cost almost the cost of the sandwich itself!

**Very disappointing experience with hygiene**

I visited Amélie’s French Bakery today and was quite disappointed to see flies on the desserts displayed on the counter. I politely asked the cashier why they weren’t covered, or why they didn’t do something to prevent flies from landing on them—especially since the dessert they’re currently promoting had a fly sitting right on top of it the entire time I stood there waiting to pay (over a minute), and no one did anything about it.

The cashier’s response was that it’s the manager’s decision — they want to promote their new dessert by displaying it uncovered on the counter, and there's nothing they can do about it. She did say she would let them know, but it seems like nothing has been done to address the issue.

It’s really unpleasant to see that in a place where people go to enjoy a treat. I’m concerned about the lack of attention to hygiene and I truly hope they take steps to fix this. It’s unacceptable for food to be exposed like that.

The biggest problem were the kids meals. Most kids do not like any bread but white bread. Amelies makes a kids PB&J with sourdough. Both kids commented about the bread. They said the sandwich was yucky. The adults tasted it and agreed. From now on, this place will only be for desserts and coffee. Also, many people drink water. Why is there a quart size pitcher to pour from? This looks really time consuming for the servers to keep filling this. Buy a dispenser or bigger container.

Putting items in a box is doing the bare minimum and should not accrue a service charge. If you do stay and sit, a server will drop off your food, but no one comes back to check on you. Be aware of that when checking out. This is not a full-service restaurant. There are no refills and you clear your own dishes and put them in a bin. If workers are unhappy with how they're being compensated, then they need to speak to management. Restaurants and cafes do have the ability to turn off this tip feature and the screen, however they choose not to.

I really enjoyed my visit to this Amélie's Café--it's much more spacious than other locations I've been to, which made it feel airy and inviting. The space stays true to their French eclectic aesthetic, filled with whimsical, vintage-inspired artwork that adds a quirky charm.

The staff at the pastry counter were friendly and helpful, which made browsing their baked goods a treat. Unfortunately, the experience at the coffee station was less warm--the woman working there wasn't as welcoming, which was a slight disappointment.

We ordered a tiramisu latte, which was just okay--not bad, but not especially memorable. We also tried a half-dozen macarons, and those were hit or miss depending on the flavor. Favorites were the raspberry, café au lait, and birthday cake, while the lavender lemon, blueberry cheesecake, and lemon tasted a bit too artificial and overly sweet.

One thing I did notice was that the tables weren't wiped down well, it was still kind of sticky, even though the café wasn't busy at the time. That said, the overall vibe was cozy and relaxed--a lovely place to enjoy a drink and pastries while catching up with friends.

The final product looked nothing like what we ordered or the picture shown to us. Very disappointing service and no attempt to make it right. Very poorly made cake and service. Even the presentation is poor; we asked for the berries to be in the center.

The staff did not engage at all. A staff-member asked if everyone was waiting on online or to-go orders. One lady got her attention… but after that, they disengaged. The 10-foot rule is apparently not a thing here. Several staff members passed by with zero acknowledgment of my existence. Again, my order was ready… I was almost to the point of going behind the counter and grabbing it myself! Someone finally asked my name but then disappeared into the kitchen with a dine-in order for someone else. Then, they grabbed another dish for someone else before finally handing me my food. Literally, It would have taken 2 seconds to just hand me my bag! This is not the first time this, or a similar instance, has happened before. I got the notification at 11:23 that my order was ready and it was not placed in my hand until 11:45. All the while, it was sitting on the back counter! The food was excellent! It always is. The kitchen staff is amazing! However… unless I am a dine-in customer… no one seems interested in being helpful. I just don’t think I am going to come back for a while again. I stopped coming after a similar instance happened a while back… only that time they said they put my food on the to-go rack but did not. I was there waiting. I really do like the food… it’s just not worth the frustration when I can just go to Chicken Salad Chick and grab my food from the pickup station.
